 Oslo Asset Management Asa Cut First Solar (FSLR) Position; Arconic (ARNC) SI Decreased By 10.34% - The San Times      
            TrendingMarketFinanceContactPrivacy PolicyOslo Asset Management Asa Cut First Solar (FSLR) Position; Arconic (ARNC) SI Decreased By 10.34% July 24, 2017 - By Peter Erickson Oslo Asset Management Asa decreased First Solar Inc (FSLR) stake by 48.9% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Oslo Asset Management Asa sold 20,000 shares as First Solar Inc (FSLR)’s stock rose 4.31%. The Oslo Asset Management Asa holds 20,900 shares with $671,000 value, down from 40,900 last quarter. First Solar Inc now has $4.59 billion valuation. The stock decreased 2.42% or $1.12 during the last trading session, reaching $45.15. About 10 shares traded. First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) has declined 22.83% since July 24, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 39.53% the S&P500.     Arconic Incorporated (NYSE:ARNC) had a decrease of 10.34% in short interest. ARNC’s SI was 17.47 million shares in July as released by FINRA. Its down 10.34% from 19.48 million shares previously. With 2.57 million avg volume, 7 days are for Arconic Incorporated (NYSE:ARNC)’s short sellers to cover ARNC’s short positions. The SI to Arconic Incorporated’s float is 4.5%. The stock increased 1.86% or $0.46 during the last trading session, reaching $25.21. About 74 shares traded. Arconic Inc (NYSE:ARNC) has risen 34.47% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 17.77% the S&P500.Since February 23, 2017, it had 1 insider buy, and 5 selling transactions for $337,428 activity. 4,000 shares valued at $147,542 were bought by PRESBY J THOMAS on Thursday, May 11. Another trade for 2,747 shares valued at $96,145 was made by Schumaker Bryan Robert on Wednesday, May 3. Another trade for 571 shares valued at $18,569 was made by Bradley Alexander R. on Friday, March 10. $286,095 worth of First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) shares were sold by KALETA PAUL J.Investors sentiment increased to 0.87 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.10, from 0.77 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 54 investors sold FSLR shares while 104 reduced holdings. 37 funds opened positions while 100 raised stakes. 64.88 million shares or 9.40% more from 59.30 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. 183,595 are held by Sg Americas Ltd Liability Corp. Cibc Asset Management owns 0% invested in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) for 9,237 shares. Hap Trading Ltd Llc has 0.07% invested in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) for 44,900 shares. Laurion Management Limited Partnership reported 80,000 shares. Geode Capital Ltd Liability Corporation holds 0.01% of its portfolio in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) for 790,674 shares. Asset Management One Commerce Limited holds 10,793 shares. First Interstate Comml Bank invested 0% in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR). Riverhead Mgmt Ltd Liability Com owns 0.02% invested in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) for 10,567 shares. Clear Harbor Asset Ltd Liability Co reported 16,955 shares. Oregon Employees Retirement Fund has 7,833 shares for 0.01% of their portfolio. Parkside Retail Bank has invested 0% in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR). Zevin Asset Mngmt Ltd Limited Liability Company has invested 0.21% in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR). The Cayman Islands-based Quantres Asset Management has invested 1.29% in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR). The Sweden-based Nordea Inv Management Ab has invested 0.01% in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR). Hightower Advsr Ltd Limited Liability Company invested 0.01% of its portfolio in First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR).Analysts await First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) to report earnings on August, 2. They expect $-0.05 earnings per share, down 105.75% or $0.92 from last year’s $0.87 per share. After $0.25 actual earnings per share reported by First Solar, Inc. for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -120.00% negative EPS growth.Among 25 analysts covering First Solar Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR), 7 have Buy rating, 4 Sell and 14 Hold. Therefore 28% are positive. First Solar Inc. had 56 analyst reports since August 5, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Standpoint Research downgraded the stock to “Hold” rating in Thursday, February 25 report. Deutsche Bank maintained First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) rating on Tuesday, April 26. Deutsche Bank has “Buy” rating and $80 target. Roth Capital initiated the stock with “Buy” rating in Tuesday, January 26 report. JP Morgan maintained the shares of FSLR in report on Tuesday, August 4 with “Buy” rating. The stock of First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) earned “Neutral” rating by Mizuho on Thursday, March 31. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Wednesday, November 18 by Deutsche Bank. The company was initiated on Friday, November 6 by Macquarie Research. Goldman Sachs maintained the shares of FSLR in report on Tuesday, August 16 with “Buy” rating. The stock of First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) has “Hold” rating given on Thursday, August 6 by TheStreet. The stock of First Solar, Inc. (NASDAQ:FSLR) earned “Buy” rating by Standpoint Research on Friday, October 30.Arconic Inc., formerly Alcoa Inc., is engaged in lightweight metals engineering and manufacturing. The company has market cap of $11.32 billion. The Firm operates through three divisions: Global Rolled Products, Engineered Products and Solutions, and Transportation and Construction Solutions. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s multi-material products, which include aluminum, titanium and nickel, are used around the world in markets, such as aerospace, automotive, commercial transportation and packaging.Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our FREE daily email newsletter.       Free Email NewsletterEnter your email address below to get the latest news and analysts' ratings for your stocks with our free daily email newsletter:   Recent Posts Analysts See $0.05 EPS for ClearOne Incoprorated (CLRO), Eaton Vance Floating-rate Income Trust (EFT) Has 0.96 Sentiment As Pepsico (PEP) Stock Rose, Nbt Bank N A Cut Position by $305,032